<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41894888</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>04</Month><Day>03</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>04</Month><Day>03</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1873-3778</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>1775</Volume><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>May</Month><Day>24</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Journal of chromatography. A</Title><ISOAbbreviation>J Chromatogr A</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Development of a magnetic solid phase extraction method using a molecularly imprinted polymer@magnetic bimetallic metal-organic framework nanocomposite for the extraction of acetamiprid pesticide from honey samples.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>466843</StartPage><MedlinePgn>466843</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.chroma.2026.466843</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0021-9673(26)00173-1</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>In this study, a nanocomposite based on MIP@ZrZnMOF@Fe&#x2083;O&#x2084; has been synthesized and employed as a sorbent in magnetic solid phase extraction method performed in a narrow bore tube. The suggested method is used for the extraction of acetamiprid from commercial honey samples before its quantification with liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry. In this work, the sorbent particles (at mg-level) are added into diluted honey solution placed in a narrow bore tube. By doing so, the sorbent particles move down through the tube under gravity force and adsorb the analyte. In the subsequent, the sedimented particles are transferred to the top of the solution with the help of a magnet and released again to move down through the tube. This procedure is repeated for five times and after that the aqueous phase is discarded and the analyte adsorbed onto the sorbent particles is eluted with a mixture of water: acetonitrile: formic acid. Finally, the eluent is taken in the presence of a magnet and injected into the determination system. Under optimum extraction conditions, extraction recovery was 83%. In the present research, forty honey samples were analyzed using the developed method to determine their acetamiprid content in order to guaranty their safety.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2026 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Jamel</LastName><ForeName>Saba H</ForeName><Initials>SH</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Chemistry, College of Education for pure Science (Ibn Al-Haitham), University of Baghdad, Baghdad, Iraq.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Jouybari</LastName><ForeName>Touraj Ahmadi</ForeName><Initials>TA</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Clinical Research Development Center, Imam Khomeini and Dr. Mohammad Kermanshahi and Farabi Hospitals, Kermanshah University of Medical Sciences, Kermanshah, Iran.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Ataee</LastName><ForeName>Mari</ForeName><Initials>M</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Clinical Research Development Center, Imam Khomeini and Dr. Mohammad Kermanshahi and Farabi Hospitals, Kermanshah University of Medical Sciences, Kermanshah, Iran.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Moradi</LastName><ForeName>Masoud</ForeName><Initials>M</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Research Center for Environmental Determinants of Health (RCEDH), Health Institute, Kermanshah University of Medical Sciences, Kermanshah, Iran.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Fattahi</LastName><ForeName>Nazir</ForeName><Initials>N</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Research Center for Environmental Determinants of Health (RCEDH